\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 User Management\

\f1\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf2 User management in PostgreSQL involves creating, modifying, and dropping user accounts (also called 
\f0\b roles
\f1\b0 ) and assigning them permissions. Roles can be a user or a group of users.\
To create a new user with a password, use the \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 CREATE ROLE\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  command.
\fs48 \cf5 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf6 \cb7 \strokec6 CREATE\cf3 \strokec3  ROLE myuser \cf6 \strokec6 WITH\cf3 \strokec3  LOGIN PASSWORD \cf8 \strokec8 'strongpassword'\cf3 \strokec3 ;\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 To grant specific permissions, use the \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 GRANT\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  command. You can grant privileges on databases, tables, schemas, and other objects.
\fs48 \cf5 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf6 \cb7 \strokec6 GRANT\cf3 \strokec3  \cf6 \strokec6 CONNECT\cf3 \strokec3  \cf6 \strokec6 ON\cf3 \strokec3  DATABASE myapp_db \cf6 \strokec6 TO\cf3 \strokec3  myuser;\
\cf6 \strokec6 GRANT\cf3 \strokec3  \cf6 \strokec6 SELECT\cf3 \strokec3 , \cf6 \strokec6 INSERT\cf3 \strokec3 , UPDATE, \cf6 \strokec6 DELETE\cf3 \strokec3  \cf6 \strokec6 ON\cf3 \strokec3  \cf6 \strokec6 TABLE\cf3 \strokec3  mytable \cf6 \strokec6 TO\cf3 \strokec3  myuser;\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 To revoke privileges, use the \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 REVOKE\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  command.
\fs48 \cf5 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf6 \cb7 \strokec6 REVOKE\cf3 \strokec3  \cf6 \strokec6 DELETE\cf3 \strokec3  \cf6 \strokec6 ON\cf3 \strokec3  \cf6 \strokec6 TABLE\cf3 \strokec3  mytable \cf6 \strokec6 FROM\cf3 \strokec3  myuser;\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 To drop a user, use \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 DROP ROLE\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 .
